<body>
    <h1>Use PHP5.4 built-in server</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <div class=3D"aui-message warning shadowed information-macro">=20
<p class=3D"title">Version compatibility</p>=20
<span class=3D"aui-icon icon-warning">Icon</span>=20
<div class=3D"message-content">=20
<p>This recipe is compatible with <strong>eZ Publish 5.2 / 2013.05</strong>=
</p>=20
</div>=20
</div>=20
<h2 id=3D"UsePHP5.4built-inserver-Description">Description</h2>
<p>PHP 5.4 comes with a <a href=3D"http://php.net/manual/en/features.comman=
dline.webserver.php" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">built-in webs=
erver for development purpose</a>. This very handy as it makes you <strong>=
kickstart development quickly</strong>, getting rid of Apache / Nginx confi=
guration hassle.&nbsp;<span style=3D"font-size: 10.0pt;line-height: 13.0pt;=
">All you need here is PHP 5.4+ with command line binary.</span></p>
<h2 id=3D"UsePHP5.4built-inserver-Usage">Usage</h2>
<p>Symfony comes with a wrapper script for booting the built-in webserver:&=
nbsp;<code><a href=3D"http://serverrun" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofo=
llow">server:run</a></code>. It's a nice shortcut as it will correctly set =
the web root depending on your configuration. However, you can't use it out=
 of the box with eZ Publish for several reasons (i.e. we don't share the sa=
me front controllers and we need specific rewrite rules).</p>=20
<div class=3D"aui-message problem shadowed information-macro">=20
<span class=3D"aui-icon icon-problem">Icon</span>=20
<div class=3D"message-content">=20
<p>Use this command for <strong>development purpose only</strong> ! <br /><=
strong>DO NOT use it in production !</strong></p>=20
</div>=20
</div>=20
<p>To be able to run this command for eZ Publish development purpose, we ne=
ed to use the provided router script which handles all the rewrite rules fo=
r you.</p>
<p>The following example will start the webserver on <code>localhost:8000</=
code>, so you'll be able to run your eZ application by going to&nbsp;<a hre=
f=3D"http://localhost:8000" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">http:/=
/localhost:8000</a>&nbsp;from your browser.</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"theme: Eclipse; brush: bash; gutter: false" style=3D"font-siz=
e:12px;">php ezpublish/console server:run -r ../bin/ezrouter.php localhost:=
8000</pre>=20
</div>
</div>=20
<div class=3D"aui-message hint shadowed information-macro">=20
<span class=3D"aui-icon icon-hint">Icon</span>=20
<div class=3D"message-content">=20
<p><code>../bin/ezrouter.php</code><span style=3D"color: rgb(51,51,51);">&n=
bsp;is needed because with&nbsp;</span><code>server:run</code><span style=
=3D"color: rgb(51,51,51);">&nbsp;command, working directory is&nbsp;</span>=
<code>web/</code><span style=3D"color: rgb(51,51,51);">.</span></p>=20
</div>=20
</div>
    </div>
</body>
